40|$|The book {{tells the}} history of how, and why Arnold Schoenberg invented his serial musical style. It {{collects}} every musical score, every writing, every letter, every other document to reconstruct the way followed by the composer between 1912 and 1925. First, the author discovered even in the Jakobsleiter a twelve <b>tones</b> <b>row</b> never noticed before. Other unreliable, philosophical, political, biased studies on Schoenberg are criticized...|$|R
