50|$|Although some of Lulu is freely composed, Berg {{also makes}} use of his teacher Arnold Schoenberg's twelve-tone technique. Rather than using one <b>tone</b> <b>row</b> for the entire work, however, he gives each {{character}} {{his or her own}} <b>tone</b> <b>row,</b> meaning that the tone rows act rather like the leitmotifs in Richard Wagner's operas.|$|E
